-- Ex-divs to take 1.5 points off FTSE 100 on Sep. 10 
-- By Atul Prakash
-- Mon Sep 08, 2014 09:59AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 8 (Reuters) - The following FTSE 100 <.FTSE> companies will go ex-dividend on Wednesday, after which investors will no longer qualify for the latest dividend payout.     According to Reuters calculations at current market prices, the effect of  the resulting adjustment to prices by market-makers would take 1.54 points off  the index.

